ID  - 28673586
T1  - Potential therapeutic effect of alkaline reduced water in polycystic ovarian syndrome.
DO  - https://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.mehy.2017.05.017
A1  - Ara, Jesmin
A1  - Nuwormegbe, Selikem Abla
A1  - Sajo, Ma Easter Joy
A1  - Kim, Soo-Ki
A1  - Shim, Kwang-Yong
A1  - Lee, Kyu-Jae
Y1  - 2017//
Y2  - 20170524//
N2  - Polycystic ovarian syndrome (PCOS) is an endocrine-metabolic disorder characterized by hormonal disturbances including hyperandrogenemia, insulin resistance, and hyperinsulinemia culminating into obesity, multiple ovarian cysts and anovulatory infertility in women. There has been no effective medication against PCOS and its complication. However, weight loss can reduce insulin resistance, which in turn helps to restore hormonal balance and ovulation resulting to improved fertility. Previously, we reported that alkaline reduced water (ARW) could significantly reduce obesity by alleviating adiposity, regulating the levels of adipokines/pro-inflammatory cytokines and by inducing cholesterol homeostasis. Herein, we hypothesize that ARW might ameliorate the pathophysiological (hormonal, metabolic, and immunological) imbalances incurred by PCOS, thereby improving the infertility of PCOS patients. Copyright © 2017 Elsevier Ltd. All rights reserved.
